schema.description:
Server-Sent Events stream containing JSON events with the following structure:
- Event format: data: {"type": "event-type", "payload": {...}}

Channel Types:
1. "user" - Subscribe to user-specific events:
    start-stream: {"type": "start-stream", "payload": {"streamId": "string", "userId": "string"}}
    stop-stream: {"type": "stop-stream", "payload": {"streamId": "string", "userId": "string"}}
    new-clip: {"type": "new-clip", "payload": {"clipId": "string", "clipperId": "string", "userId": "string"}}
    gems-updated: {"type": "gems-updated", "payload": {"userId": "string", "gems": number}}
    stream-likes-count-updated: {"type": "stream-likes-count-updated", "payload": {"streamId": "string", "userId": "string", "count": number}}
    in-app-notification: {"type": "in-app-notification", "payload": {...notification details...}}

2. "token:{address}" or "token:my" - Subscribe to token activity events:
    token-activity: {"type": "token-activity", "payload": {"userAddress": "string", "type": "buy|sell|...", "amount": number, "signature": "string", "createdAt": "ISO string", "user": {...user object...}, "token": null}}

Connection stays open and events are pushed in real-time as they occur.
